      "comment": "CHEEKY MILA (2) had been racing in honest fashion recording two placings in a row before finishing seventh (23.36) at Shepparton latest. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Has ability and can bounce back. COUSIN JOHNNY (7) finished second (22.48) two back at Ballarat but out of the placings last time when 6th at Horsham. Boasts two wins from four starts out of this box. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. PAW WYLDER (8) took the sit on the lead from an outside box but levelled up and drew clear to score (24.51) at this track in a Bottom Up - Maiden over 425m. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. CALLAHAN (4) has definite claims at his first try at this circuit.",
